+---
+verdict: REQUEST_CHANGES
+summary: Proposed flock design regresses existing lock-file semantics and can break mutual exclusion on release.
+findings:
+  - "prd/tech-design.md:25: On fcntl platforms, acquire() ignores an existing lock file containing a live PID unless another process currently holds a flock on the same inode. That contradicts the unchanged tests and existing semantics: test_acquire_already_locked_different_pid_alive writes PID 1 and expects acquire() to return False, but the proposed code would acquire the flock and return True."
